# Auto Commit and Sync After Changes

After any code or config change: commit on a topic branch, push, open/update PR to `main`, and complete the full ship bar.

1. Branch: `git checkout -b agent/<slug>` from fresh `origin/main` (unless already on a topic branch or user ordered `main` hotfix).
2. Stage and commit: `git add <paths> && git commit -m "<description>"`.
3. Push: `git push -u origin HEAD`.
4. Complete the full ship bar: `git-pr-workflow-default.mdc` (all 9 steps inline there).

Do not leave uncommitted or unpushed changes unless the user explicitly asks to stop before syncing.
